This paper is likely to belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category as it describes the design and implementation of a deep learning platform that manages and executes DL training jobs at scale. It is also likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories as it discusses the use of deep learning in various application domains. Additionally, the paper may belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category as it examines the dependability, scalability, and efficiency of the platform. Finally, it may also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category as it discusses the scheduling policies used in the platform.
